      <title>Downward scaling tools?  How about -1DI scaling being looked at on the class issues list.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=14273#M14273</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;If each fight lasts ~40 seconds, mob Triples, hits 66% of the time, every 2 seconds, mob gets a hit once a second, so warrior negates 1 DI per second.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Paladin Heals&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Touch of Piety is 1714 pre-focus and pre AA... post focus average its 2050.  1 cast per 40 second fight alone is equal to a -1DI of about 51.  DB 1 DI 51=1021 max hits.   So any mob with a max hit of 1020 or less a pally tanks better than a warrior casting 1 heal per 40 second fight.  2 Heals raises the DI to 102(2041 Max hit)  My shaman twink can drop 2K mana pre-AA/Spec/Focus per fight and stay up in mana during most grind groups until bathroom breaks, respawn pauses, etc.  2 stuns- Ancient Force of Jeron,  Force of Piety, and 2 casts of Touch of Piety is 1302 mana pre-AA/Focus/Specialization.  2 Pained Memory, and half of Canni V will net my shaman back about 1253 mana per fight, but also require another 420 spent, so a net return of 833 for a net spent during a fight of about 1170.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Shadowknight Taps&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ancient Bite of Muram Recourse-  +135 mana, Inruku's Bite recourse  +130 mana.  265 mana per fight cast, IF both are cast once per fight,  after 1.5 fights a cleric will have what ammounts to a mana free CH to cast.  , that means for 9600hp to even EQUAL -1DI, You're looking at a DI of 160 - (DB1 DI 160 max hit 3201)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So 2 Bite recourses to a cleric will flat out DESTROY -1DI in non-defensive content.... Requireing at minimum a mob with a DI of 160.  Two Paladin heals will negate -1DI  requiring a DI of 102 or better.  To be completely fair, a fight will be marginally shorter with a warrior tanking than a paladin tanking depending on how long it takes the DPS classes to ramp up with the initial snap agro availability, plus of course (for an SK) the bonus mana for a DD class being able to get another DD in (essentially mana free) every so often.  (Time/Damage varies on class, AA, and Focus)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;What this basically means isn't that knights are broken, what it means is:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Paladins probably need a minor boost.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;-1DI hasn't scaled at all similar to the increase in spell efficiency&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;This should probably be looked at.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Whatever solution is chosen should be a long term self scaling solution that isn't Expanion era or mob DPS dependant.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;-1DI is the part that's broken, not Paladin heals, or SK Taps.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
