    <item>
      <title>Re: Downward scaling tools?  How about -1DI scaling being looked at on the class issues list.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=warriorbalance&amp;message.id=15705#M15705</link>
      <description>&lt;span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Frodlin wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Downward scaling is very important, as getting tools which are more upward scaling acheives nothing in group content, and further separates an already pretty high gap on raid content.   It's a mistake not to go the route of Aura of Runes.    The issue is.. you want something that will help in group content, which AoR would do if it were useful, yet be immaterial to raids, which AoR would be.    The two new Knight skills do not scale at all, they're more powerful the less damage a mob does.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In order to change innate mitigation to match that, you can blow out of the water the tanking balance as NPC's hit harder.   &lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;I agree with you here on points, but I think the &amp;quot;gap&amp;quot; generated by PoR spells is not nearly as significant as you are thinking it is. From what I understand about procs and procrate mods and how they work... Lucy has WoT and DS at a procratemod of 400, my understanding is that you will take the base proc rate (2ppm) and treat the mod as a percentage gain/loss. So in this case you have a base rate of 8 procs per minute. 4 procs in most single group fights of around 30 seconds (grind content). Conversely Mock will fire twice in the same fight, so Decrepit Skin is avoiding 1000 damage per fight will mock is avoiding 500. That's assuming though optimal conditions for Decrepit Skin that simply don't exist in group content. For one you have mobs that flee at 20% in most grind content, right there that means 20% of each fight I'm not getting hit and so Decrepid Skin has 0% chance of proccing 20% of the time. So that 1000ish per fight is really more like 800 per fight, or 300 more then Mock per fight, 600 more per minute or 10 DPS. That's not even figuring in for caster mobs who further aren't attacking each time they cast and thus not triggering procs, casters are fairly common in single group stuff and on average they cast alot.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now 10dps is certainly a gap, but it's not an insurmountable gap. I am extremely opposed to the thought of revamping old warrior discs to close a gap formed specifically from PoR abilities, if the gap is not acceptable it needs to be addressed by mock and champion's aura. If AoR is not worth it then it needs to be balanced versus omens SK abilities, not PoR ones. As far as endurance versus mana (because I know you are going to bring this up) Mock is not an additive endurance expenditure, it's the exact same endurance as Bazu is and it's an alternative endurance expenditure. It's cost is not so much needed to be balanced up again Decrepit Skin, as it is needed to be balanced versus Bazu, because whether you are mocking or not you are spending the same 350 endurance every 30 seconds. Simply adding a 3rd hit to Mock's rune recourse would effectively remove any gap between the two abilities.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
